From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000024 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: PDF Note Workspace <local@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 01:25:00 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] Use LocalAppData instead of Documents as Windows home

The conversion runtime is used headlessly with an explicit UserInstallation
profile.  Treating the Windows Documents known folder as the generic home
directory causes Controlled Folder Access to block soffice.bin during
conversion startup, even when Work/Backup/Temp paths are redirected.

Use LocalAppData for the Windows home directory fallback so custom headless
conversion does not attempt to create or modify the protected Documents
folder.
---
 sal/osl/w32/security.cxx | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/sal/osl/w32/security.cxx b/sal/osl/w32/security.cxx
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/sal/osl/w32/security.cxx
+++ b/sal/osl/w32/security.cxx
@@ -417,7 +417,7 @@ sal_Bool SAL_CALL osl_getHomeDir(oslSecurity Security, rtl_uString **pustrDirect
 
     OUString aSysDir = pSecImpl->m_pNetResource
                            ? OUString(o3tl::toU(pSecImpl->m_pNetResource->lpRemoteName))
-                           : GetSpecialFolder(FOLDERID_Documents);
+                           : GetSpecialFolder(FOLDERID_LocalAppData);
 
     return !aSysDir.isEmpty()
            && osl_File_E_None == osl_getFileURLFromSystemPath(aSysDir.pData, pustrDirectory);
